quran[6]{c,v,t}:
  3,181,"Indeed, God has heard those ˹among the Jews˺ who said, “God is poor; we are rich!” We have certainly recorded their slurs and their killing of prophets unjustly. Then We will say, “Taste the torment of burning"
  3,182,This is ˹the reward˺ for what your hands have done. And God is never unjust to ˹His˺ creation.”
  3,183,"Those ˹are the same people˺ who say, “God has commanded us not to believe in any messenger unless he brings us an offering to be consumed by fire ˹from the sky˺.” Say, ˹O Prophet,˺ “Other prophets did in fact come to you before me with clear proofs and ˹even˺ what you demanded—why then did you kill them, if what you say is true?”"
  3,184,"If you are rejected by them, so too were messengers before you who came with clear proofs, divine Books, and enlightening Scriptures"
  3,185,"Every soul will taste death. And you will only receive your full reward on the Day of Judgment. Whoever is spared from the Fire and is admitted into Paradise will ˹indeed˺ triumph, whereas the life of this world is no more than the delusion of enjoyment"
  3,186,"You ˹believers˺ will surely be tested in your wealth and yourselves, and you will certainly hear many hurtful words from those who were given the Scripture before you and ˹from˺ the polytheists. But if you are patient and mindful ˹of God˺—surely this is a resolve to aspire to"